														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865515">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Humanoid entity with metallic skin</li>
<li>Reaction to people it encounters depends on their morality</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> The SCP was once a normal human woman, possibly someone who worked for the Foundation, who was badly mutilated and killed in an accident that may or may not have involved another SCP. A few hours after her death, her body spontaneously reanimated and morphed into a large humanoid entity with skin that appeared to be made of metal. It was then taken into Foundation custody, where its abilities and personality became apparent during testing.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> The SCP's gimmick is that it reacts differently to people it encounters depending on what it perceives their morality to be. Upon looking at a person it encounters, it can instantly gauge their morality, though the standards by which it defines good and evil aren't entirely understood. If it sees someone as not being evil, it will typically ignore them, but if it sees someone as evil, it experiences a dramatic increase in aggression, often attempting to kill them.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> If anyone has any feedback or suggestions as to how I could elaborate upon or improve the idea, I'd be glad to hear it. If the idea is too similar to an existing SCP, please let me know, since I might not be aware since there are so many SCPs.</p>

							</div>

								
					
